episodes.name: Ann Widdecombe and Craig Revel Horwood

episodes.name: Tina Hobley and Sharon Maughan
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Former Holby City actors Tina Hobley and Sharon Maughan traverse the beautiful Cotswold countryside in search of some classy antiques.

episodes.name: Anthea Turner and Andi Peters
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Television presenters Anthea Turner and Andi Peters team up with Road Trip favourites Charles Hanson and Margie Cooper.

episodes.name: Cliff Parisi and Judy Parfitt
episodes.overview: Call the Midwife actors Cliff Parisi and Judy Parfitt hunt Kent for antiques to sell at an auction in Norfolk. Will a padouk table or a railway lamp make the biggest profit?

episodes.name: Anna Chancellor and Holly Aird
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Actors Anna Chancellor and Holly Aird are joined by experts Natasha Raskin Sharp and Margie Cooper in the Home Counties.

episodes.name: John Sergeant and Peter White
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Broadcasting veterans John Sergeant and Peter White are in Surrey to test their antiquing skills with Philip Serrell and James Braxton.

episodes.name: Pam Ayres and Geoffrey Whitehead
episodes.overview: Pam Ayres and Geoffrey Whitehead are making inroads into the world of antiques as they head towards an auction in Cirencester alongside experts Kate Bliss and James Braxton.

episodes.name: Brian Conley and Nick Owen
episodes.overview: Brian Conley and Nick Owen scour Shropshire for antique treasure with experts Phil Serrell and Kate Bliss. But what are the local connections to Napoleon and the White House?

episodes.name: David Gower and Nick Hancock
episodes.overview: Old pals David Gower and Nick Hancock are joined by Charlie Ross and Phil Serrell on a Road Trip through Hampshire on the hunt for antiques, with some surprising results.

episodes.name: Danny Crates and Liz Johnson
episodes.overview: Paralympians Danny Crates and Liz Johnson shop their way around Suffolk and Essex. Will a Victorian table or a meerschaum pipe secure the biggest profit?

episodes.name: Derek Fowlds and Bill Simons
episodes.overview: Derek Fowlds and Bill Simons set off from Helmsley, North Yorkshire. Derek charms his way to some discounts. Bill's eye for the unusual secures him some unexpected lots.

episodes.name: Grace Dent and Amol Rajan
episodes.overview: Journalists Grace Dent and Amol Rajan search East Anglia for profitable antiques. They purchase Winston Churchill's cigar and a wind-up toy rocket, hoping for big profits.

episodes.name: Tim Vine and Ricky Grover
episodes.overview: Tim Vine and Ricky Grover search for profitable antiques in Scotland. The teams gamble on a mahogany chair and pewter candle sticks, but a unique duck gives Ricky a problem.

episodes.name: Felicity Montagu and Clare Holman
episodes.overview: The stars in the vintage cars are actors Felicity Montagu and Clare Holman. With the help of James Braxton and Arusha Irvine, they mosey around the Midlands in search of antiques.

episodes.name: Valerie Singleton and Diane Louise Jordan
episodes.overview: Blue Peter's Valerie Singleton and Diane Louise Jordan compete to find profitable antiques. One team plump for an elephant and an eagle in a bid to make a lot of money at auction.

episodes.name: Roberta Taylor and Trudie Goodwin
episodes.overview: Roberta Taylor and Trudie Goodwin charge around Stirlingshire. Norwegian silver catches the eye of one celebrity, while the other is influenced by the taste for gin.

episodes.name: Linford Christie and Katharine Merry
episodes.overview: Linford Christie and Katharine Merry race to make the most money from antiques. Linford pins his hopes on a tiny brooch, despite it costing a three-figure sum.

7.name: Series 7
7.overview: Celebrities travel round the country in vintage cars hunting antiques to sell at auction.

episodes.name: Denise van Outen and Kelly Brook
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Denise van Outen faces off with Kelly Brook. Kelly may have home advantage, but Denise's haggling skills make the result hard to call.

episodes.name: Jordan Banjo and Perri Kiely
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Jordan Banjo and Perri Kiely take time off from Diversity to get behind the wheel of a classic car and head out into the country.

episodes.name: David Bradley and Nigel Harman
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Actors David Bradley and Nigel Harman head out on the highways from Oxfordshire to Somerset in search of antique goodies.

episodes.name: Al Murray and Paul Chowdhry
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Comics Al Murray and Paul Chowdhry hunt for antiques that will make a profit at auction, with James Braxton and Natasha Raskin Sharp.

episodes.name: Ian 'H' Watkins and Claire Sweeney
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Pop star Ian 'H' Watkins and entertainer Claire Sweeney scour the Welsh border for antiques, aided by James Braxton and David Harper.

episodes.name: Peter Andre and Joe Pasquale
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Showbiz mates Peter Andre and Joe Pasquale sample the joys of the Kent seaside.

episodes.name: Janey Lee Grace and Tim Smith
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Radio presenters and chums Janey Lee Grace and Tim Smith seek treasure amongst the Cotswolds and the Malverns.

episodes.name: Richard Coles and Joe McFadden
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Rev Richard Coles and Strictly co-pilot Joe McFadden romp across Scotland with antiques experts David Harper and Phil Serrell.

episodes.name: John Partridge and Anita Harris
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Stars of stage and screen John Partridge and Anita Harris road trip around Lancashire and Yorkshire.

episodes.name: Russell Kane and AJ Odudu
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Comedian Russell Kane and presenter AJ Odudu take to the road with antiquers Phil Serrell and Margie Cooper.

episodes.name: Anneka Rice and Liz Carr
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Anneka Rice's latest challenge is competing against Silent Witness actor Liz Carr in a competition to find the most profitable antique.

episodes.name: Sherrie Hewson and Tony Maudsley
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Benidorm buddies Sherrie Hewson and Tony Maudsley have left sun-soaked Spain to seek fortune in Leicestershire and Nottinghamshire.

episodes.name: Charlotte Smith and Tom Heap
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Countryfile stars Charlotte Smith and Tom Heap swap agriculture for antiques as they treasure-seek in Hampshire and Buckinghamshire.

episodes.name: Rebecca Adlington and Helen Skelton
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Rebecca Adlington and Helen Skelton treasure-seek in the north west with help from Roo Irvine and Tim Medhurst.

episodes.name: Charles Hanson and Natasha Raskin Sharp
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Sam and Mark hit the antiques trail with Charles Hanson and Natasha Raskin Sharp in Yorkshire.

episodes.name: Sara Dallin and Keren Woodward
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Bananarama's Sara Dallin and Keren Woodward are on tour with Charles Hanson and David Harper in the south east of England.

episodes.name: Nadia Sawalha and Kaye Adams
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Nadia Sawalha and Kaye Adams visit the antique shops of Edinburgh and beyond.

episodes.name: Sue Johnston and Lisa Riley
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Sue Johnston and Lisa Riley hit north west England in a whirlwind of hilarity and haggling with Catherine Southon and David Harper.

episodes.name: Rav Wilding and Martel Maxwell
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques. Rav Wilding is guilty of never having been in an antiques shop! That is all going to change as he joins Martel Maxwell on a trip through Cheshire.

episodes.name: Michelle Ackerley and Russell Grant
episodes.overview: Celebrities hunt for antiques across the UK. Michelle Ackerley and Russell Grant chum up with Roo Irvine and Phil Serrell for an antiques jolly on the hottest days of the summer.

8.name: Series 8
8.overview: Celebrities travel round the country in vintage cars hunting antiques to sell at auction.

episodes.name: Judy Murray and Greg Rusedski
episodes.overview: Judy Murray and Greg Rusedski swap the tennis court for Caledonia on a hunt for antiques with Angus Ashworth and Raj Bisram. Do they really find Andy Murray’s old clogs?

episodes.name: Craig Charles and Robert Llewellyn
episodes.overview: Craig Charles and Robert Llewellyn team up with antiquers Izzie Balmer and Tim Medhurst for a West Midlands road trip. A search for profit-making antiques to sell at auction.

episodes.name: Dan Brocklebank and Hayley Tamaddon
episodes.overview: Actors Dan Brocklebank and Hayley Tamaddon are on the search for antiques in East Anglia. Guiding them on their way are antiques experts Raj Bisram and Angus Ashworth.

episodes.name: Keith Duffy and Brian McFadden
episodes.overview: Old friends Keith Duffy and Brian McFadden stage a battle of the boy bands. Westlife versus Boyzone - who is best with antiques? On backing vocals are experts Roo and Margie.

episodes.name: Dr Ranj Singh and Dr Zoe Williams
episodes.overview: Two of TV's favourite doctors, Dr Ranj Singh and Dr Zoe Williams, are paired with experts Steph Connell and Tim Medhurst. Both hope to catch the antiques bug in Lancashire and Greater Manchester.

episodes.name: Neil Morrissey and JJ Chalmers
episodes.overview: Actor Neil Morrissey takes on TV presenter JJ Chalmers in the antiques buying challenge. Expect a palomino horse, an old monkey, a rattling teddy and a furious farmer.

episodes.name: Dr John Cooper and Phill Jupitus
episodes.overview: Poet Dr John Cooper Clarke and comic and TV panellist Phill Jupitus seek treasure in East Anglia, with excellent expert guidance courtesy of auctioneer James Braxton and dealer Stephanie Connell.

episodes.name: Emeli Sandé and Naughty Boy
episodes.overview: Singing sensation Emeli Sande and her collaborator and chum Naughty Boy take time off from making hit records to get behind the wheel of a classic car and seek out antiques.

episodes.name: Wes Nelson and Georgia Steel
episodes.overview: Love Island stars Wes Nelson and Georgia Steel couple up with experts Izzie Balmer and Phil Serrell on the hunt for antiques in Yorkshire, before an auction in North Shields.

episodes.name: Andrea McLean and Penny Lancaster
episodes.overview: Today's treasure seekers in East Anglia are TV Loose Women Andrea McLean and Penny Lancaster, with experts Tim Medhurst and David Harper.

episodes.name: Gemma Oaten and Samantha Renke
episodes.overview: Emmerdale and Holby City actress Gemma Oaten and actress, broadcaster and disability rights campaigner Samantha Renke hunt for antiques in Lancashire with experts Philip Serrell and James Braxton.

episodes.name: Will Mellor and Nick Pickard
episodes.overview: Actors and best pals Will Mellor and Nick Pickard take a pocket watch and a ship's porthole to auction in Greenwich on advice from experts Paul Laidlaw and Stephanie Connell.

episodes.name: Rosie Marcel and Bob Barrett
episodes.overview: Holby City's Rosie Marcel and Bob Barrett swap scalpels and scrubs for curios and collectibles in a competitive Road Trip around the flatlands of Cambridgeshire and Bedfordshire.

episodes.name: Shappi Khorsandi and Konnie Huq
episodes.overview: Comedy queen Shappi Khorsandi and Blue Peter royalty Konnie Huq are in Sussex with experts Charles Hanson and Tim Medhurst. Who can make the most profit from antiques?

episodes.name: Helen Flanagan and Jorgie Porter
episodes.overview: Actresses, models and friends Helen Flanagan and Jorgie Porter pair with experts Phil Serrell and James Braxton. They uncover an interesting tea caddy and an unusual ship's compass.

episodes.name: Mariella Frostrup and Pearl Lowe
episodes.overview: Broadcaster Mariella Frostrup and designer Pearl Lowe rummage through antiques shops and uncover Norwegian jewellery, African sculpture and some traditional English furniture.

episodes.name: Adam Henson and Steve Brown
episodes.overview: Countryfile's Adam Henson and Steve Brown are on the hunt for antiques in the rolling Cotswold Hills, accompanied by experts Roo Irvine and David Harper.

episodes.name: Stanley Johnson and Georgia ‘Toff’ Toffolo
episodes.overview: Stanley Johnson and Georgia ‘Toff’ Toffolo search Cumbria for antiques with experts Paul Laidlaw and Izzie Balmer. Will a snake or a horse prove to be the most profitable?

episodes.name: Bobby Davro and Sheila Ferguson
episodes.overview: Comedian Bobby Davro and singer Sheila Ferguson are on a trip around Kent with James Braxton and Catherine Southon. Expect a firedog, a rocking horse and a green jellyfish.

episodes.name: Jamali Maddix and Bobby Mair
episodes.overview: Comedians Jamali Maddix and Bobby Mair battle for the best punchline and most profitable antique with experts Natasha Raskin-Sharp and Angus Ashworth.

9.name: Series 9
9.overview: Celebrities travel round the country in vintage cars hunting antiques to sell at auction.

episodes.name: Jerry Hall and Philippa Perry
episodes.overview: Supermodel Jerry Hall and psychotherapist and TV presenter Philippa Perry take to the road with antiques experts Tim Medhurst and Charles Hanson.

episodes.name: Clive Myrie and Reeta Chakrabarti
episodes.overview: Journalists Clive Myrie and Reeta Chakrabarti find a French casket and a rocking horse to sell at auction, while James Braxton needs no excuse to strip for a cold water dip.

episodes.name: Eamonn Holmes and Victoria Smurfit
episodes.overview: Broadcaster Eamonn Holmes and award-winning actress Victoria Smurfit find antiques in Kent with connections to Columbus and royalty, dutifully aided by experts Phil and Catherine.

episodes.name: Rachel Riley and Pasha Kovalev
episodes.overview: Countdown’s Rachel Riley competes with husband and Strictly partner Pasha Kovalev to find antiques. David and Paul assist, but will maths skills or fancy footwork win the day?

episodes.name: Danny and Dani Dyer
episodes.overview: Danny Dyer and daughter Dani join auctioneers Natasha and Phil on an antiques hunt in Essex that features pirates, a raft race, sunken treasure and a huge Chinese banquet.

episodes.name: Jeff Stelling and Chris Kamara
episodes.overview: Football pundits Jeff Stelling and Chris Kamara try competitive antiquing in Leicestershire. Along the way there’s haggling, hijinks and hard cheese before they head to auction.

episodes.name: Dom Joly and Pauline McLynn
episodes.overview: Comedian Dom Joly and actor Pauline McLynn are in Lancashire with Phil and James, buying antique bamboo and teapots. Who will have the last laugh at auction?

episodes.name: Robert Daws and Mark Curry
episodes.overview: Actors Robert Daws and Mark Curry go antique hunting in Lancashire, where they find a real-life Sherlock Holmes and join a drag queen cabaret. Antiquers Roo and Izzie offer expert advice.

episodes.name: Scarlett Moffatt and Crissy Rock
episodes.overview: Showbiz pals Scarlett Moffatt and Crissy Rock go antique hunting up north with Margie Cooper and Christina Trevanion. Expect jewellery and some very old sweeties.

episodes.name: Zoe Lyons and Noreen Khan
episodes.overview: Stand-up comedians Zoe Lyons and Noreen Khan turn their hand to antiquing in Shropshire. Along the way, there are unusual purchases, frightful detours and plenty of laughs.

episodes.name: Martin and Shirlie Kemp
episodes.overview: Eighties pop stars Martin and Shirlie Kemp make a song and dance in the West Country, and cider is involved! Martin fancies vintage, and Shirlie more shabby chic, but who is gold?

episodes.name: Radzi Chinyanganya and Karim Zeroual
episodes.overview: Children’s TV stars Radzi Chinyanganya and Karim Zeroual find antique coins, clocks and a stone duck, assisted by Paul Martin and Catherine Southon. The loser faces a gunge tank.

episodes.name: Trisha Goddard and Dr Amir Khan
episodes.overview: Trisha Goddard and Dr Amir Khan join Tim Medhurst and Izzie Balmer on a hunt for profit-making antiques. Expect dressing up, burnt-out clutches and a top-secret visit to a beehive.

episodes.name: Sam Thompson and Pete ‘The Pirate’ Wicks
episodes.overview: Reality stars and best pals Sam Thompson and Pete ‘The Pirate’ Wicks hunt for antiques in the Cotswolds. There are romantic lunches, motorbike tumbles and plenty of bargains.

episodes.name: Nikki Fox and Matt Allwright
episodes.overview: Consumer journalists Nikki Fox and Matt Allwright investigate profit-making antiques in Kent alongside expert guides Natasha Raskin Sharp and David Harper.

episodes.name: Mark Radcliffe and Edith Bowman
episodes.overview: Radio broadcasters Mark Radcliffe and Edith Bowman dip their toes into the world of antiques under the expert guidance of Natasha Raskin Sharp and Paul Martin.

episodes.name: Lucy Porter and Jenny Ryan
episodes.overview: Comedian Lucy Porter and Chaser Jenny Ryan visit antique shops in south Wales. On hand to help are experts Serhat Ahmet and Steven Moore. Expect a lost recipe and a pack of corgis.

episodes.name: Gareth Malone and YolanDa Brown
episodes.overview: Musicians Gareth Malone and YolanDa Brown join David Harper and Raj Bisram for some antique shopping in Scotland, buying a rare green pig and releasing a puffin chick into the wild.

episodes.name: Rufus Hound and Chris McCausland
episodes.overview: Comedians Rufus Hound and Chris McCausland join antiques experts Margie Cooper and Ochuko Ojiri in Merseyside. There are lots of laughs and bags of buys, but will there be profits aplenty?

episodes.name: AJ and Curtis Pritchard
episodes.overview: Ballroom brothers AJ and Curtis Pritchard take the high road through Scotland in pursuit of antiques. There’s outdoor swimming and ceilidh dancing, but who will score a ten at the auction?

10.name: Series 10
10.overview: Celebrities travel round the country in vintage cars hunting antiques to sell at auction.

episodes.name: Les Dennis and Nitin Ganatra
episodes.overview: Actor, presenter and all-round entertainer Les Dennis takes on his chum, fellow thespian and soap star Nitin Ganatra, in a contest of antique hunting skills. At their disposal, at least two classic cars from the 60s, £400 each and a couple of eager experts, David Harper and Irita Marriott.

episodes.name: Jennie Bond and Simon McCoy
episodes.overview: TV journalists and former royal correspondents Jennie Bond and Simon McCoy rummage for hidden treasures around Devon. They are accompanied by experts Margie Cooper and Raj Bisram.

episodes.name: Aljaž Škorjanec and Janette Manrara
episodes.overview: Two fleet-footed stars of the Strictly dance floor, husband and wife Aljaž Škorjanec and Janette Manrara, waltz around Oxfordshire to find profitable antiques with Izzie and David.

episodes.name: Gethin Jones and Xand Van Tulleken
episodes.overview: Presenter Gethin Jones and TV doctor Xand Van Tulleken cruise both sides of the Welsh border on the prowl for antique treasures. Will these pals fall out over a porcelain pig?

episodes.name: Kelle Bryan and Charlene White
episodes.overview: Antiquers Catherine Southon and Ochuko Ojiri are joined by Loose Women’s Kelle Bryan and Charlene White on a hunt for money-making collectibles around Essex.

episodes.name: Nina Hossain and Lucrezia Millarini
episodes.overview: Today’s star-studded shopping spree features newscasters Nina Hossain and Lucrezia Millarini. Expert advice comes from Tim Medhurst and Steven Moore.

episodes.name: Katie Piper and Adam Pearson
episodes.overview: Presenters Katie Piper and Adam Pearson rummage for antiques in Northampton. Roo and David offer expert advice, but will a little piggy make a profit at auction?

episodes.name: Duncan James and Antony Costa
episodes.overview: The boys from Blue, Duncan James and Antony Costa, join antiques experts Ochuko Ojiri and Roo Irvine on an antiques romp around the Cotswolds.

episodes.name: Francis Rossi and Linda Nolan
episodes.overview: Music legends Francis Rossi and Linda Nolan join antiques experts Philip Serrell and Natasha Raskin Sharp on an antiques pleasure cruise around Surrey and Sussex.

episodes.name: Chris Hughes and Jake Quickenden
episodes.overview: The friendship of reality TV’s Chris Hughes and Jake Quickenden is put to the test as they explore South Yorkshire’s antique shops with Izzie and Irita.

episodes.name: Esme Young and Keith Brymer Jones
episodes.overview: Rare Chinese furniture goes under the gavel as TV crafting judges Esme Young and Keith Brymer Jones compete to make the most money. With Charles Hanson and Roo Irvine.

episodes.name: Anne Hegerty and Shaun Wallace
episodes.overview: TV quizzers Anne Hegerty and Shaun Wallace are on a chase to find profit making antiques. Experts James Braxton and Margie Cooper offer the wisdom in this competition.

episodes.name: Dominic Littlewood and Melinda Messenger
episodes.overview: Dominic Littlewood and Melinda Messenger join Natasha and Tim on a hunt and haggle for profitable antiques. A cat terrifies one celebrity, and a Viking find shocks the other.

episodes.name: Eric Monkman and Bobby Seagull
episodes.overview: The knowledge of antiques experts Angus Ashworth and Phil Serrell is put to the test, as their celebrity companions are University Challenge icons Eric Monkman and Bobby Seagull.

episodes.name: Peter Gunn and Melanie Hill
episodes.overview: Soap actors Peter Gunn and Melanie Hill join experts James Braxton and David Harper on an antiques hunt. A little ballerina and a big rocking horse make their way to auction.

episodes.name: Jo Brand and Kerry Godliman
episodes.overview: Leading actor-comics Jo Brand and Kerry Godliman rummage in Kent for antiques, with experts Catherine and Steven. Papier-mache proves surprisingly popular at auction.

episodes.name: Julie Tatchell and Amanda Middleditch
episodes.overview: The Repair Shop’s Julie Tatchell and Amanda Middleditch team up with experts Tim and James. They discover rare tiny toys in Birmingham and a very long church pew in Wolverhampton.

episodes.name: Megan McKenna and James Argent
episodes.overview: Reality stars Megan McKenna and James Argent keep it real in the world of antiques, helped by experts Irita and Steven. But will their Essex charm bring profit at auction?

episodes.name: Richard Osman and Ingrid Oliver
episodes.overview: Partners in crime Richard Osman and Ingrid Oliver advance to Norfolk to battle with antiques dealers and dragons. But will German pottery or Scandinavian glass make the most money?

episodes.name: Kimberly Wyatt and Ryan Thomas
episodes.overview: Pussycat Doll Kimberly Wyatt goes up against her best pal, Corrie star Ryan Thomas, in a battle to find profitable antiques. Expert help comes from Natasha Raskin-Sharp and Serhat Ahmet.

11.name: Series 11
11.overview: Antiques experts accompany celebrities on a road trip around B-road Britain.

episodes.name: Paul Merton v Suki Webster
episodes.overview: Paul Merton and his wife, fellow comic improviser Suki Webster, rummage around Kent with experts Margie Cooper and Charles Hanson.

episodes.name: Geeta Guru-Murthy v Krishnan Guru-Murthy
episodes.overview: The celebrities are news-presenting siblings Krishnan and Geeta Guru-Murthy. The journalists visit antique shops in a 1965 Ford Mustang.

episodes.name: Ian McElhinney v Tara Lynne O'Neill
episodes.overview: Two stars of hit comedy series Derry Girls go head-to-head. Actors Tara Lynne O’Neill and Ian McElhinney pop to the shops of Aberdeenshire in their sporty 1970s MGB GT, impersonating cows en route. They each have a kitty of £400 and guides in the form of Paul Laidlaw and Natasha Raskin Sharp.

episodes.name: Dianne Buswell v Owain Wyn Evans
episodes.overview: Strictly Come Dancing’s Dianne Buswell and presenter Owain Wyn Evans visit the antique shops of south Wales in a 1967 Austin Princess Vanden Plas along with experts Hettie Jago and David Harper

episodes.name: Brenda Edwards v Linda Robson
episodes.overview: Loose Women's Brenda Edwards and Linda Robson turn the antique shops of Hertfordshire upside down in their search for bargains in their Bentley Turbo R with the help of James Braxton and Serhat Ahmet.

episodes.name: Bobby Friction v Sima Kotecha
episodes.overview: Journalist Sima Kotecha and DJ Bobby Friction are in Northamptonshire and Oxfordshire in a 1967 Daimler Sovereign, with experts Roo Irvine and Philip Serrell assisting.

episodes.name: Ekin-Su Cülcüloglu v Davide Saclimenti
episodes.overview: Love Island victors Ekin-Su Cülcüloglu and Davide Sanclimenti, along with experts Izzie Balmer and Tim Medhurst, scour for antiques in a canary yellow 1970s VW motorhome.

episodes.name: Wynne Evans v Joanna Page
episodes.overview: Paired with Gavin and Stacey’s Joanna Page is opera singer and star of a certain online insurance advert Wynne Evans. They rummage in the antiques shops of south Wales.

episodes.name: Sara Davies v Amy Dowden
episodes.overview: Dragons’ Den star Sara Davies and Strictly’s Amy Dowden visit the antique shops of north east England in a 1985 Ford Cortina, with the help of Natasha Raskin Sharp and Steven Moore.

episodes.name: Amanda Barrie v Stephanie Beacham
episodes.overview: Actors Amanda Barrie and Stephanie Beacham are joined by experts Tim Medhurst and Serhat Ahmet as they hunt for antiques in Somerset in a 420 G Jaguar.

episodes.name: Samantha Fox v Sinitta
episodes.overview: Kent and Surrey host pop royalty Samantha Fox and Sinitta for their road trip in a 1987 Locus Excel. The powers behind the throne are Steven Moore and Tim Medhurst.

episodes.name: Gemma Collins v Melvin Odoom
episodes.overview: Towie’s Gemma Collins and radio DJ Melvin Odoom join experts James Braxton and Margie Cooper to hunt for antiques in a Rolls Royce Silver Shadow.

episodes.name: Richard McCourt v Dominic Wood
episodes.overview: Former hosts of CBBC’s legendary Dick and Dom in Da Bungalow, Richard McCourt and Dominic Wood, have each other in their sights in this celebrity antiques showdown.

episodes.name: Tricia Penrose v Dean Sullivan
episodes.overview: Heartbeat legend Tricia Penrose and Brookside legend Dean Sullivan travel around the streets of Liverpool, understudied by antiques experts Ishy Khan and Roo Irvine.

episodes.name: David Blunkett v Lesley Garrett
episodes.overview: Sheffield-born Labour peer Lord David Blunkett takes on soprano superstar Lesley Garrett CBE across Yorkshire in a 1966 Volvo Amazon estate, joined by experts Natasha Raskin Sharp and Margie Cooper.

episodes.name: Eshaan Akbar v Tez Ilyas
episodes.overview: Comedians Tez Ilyas and Eshaan Akbar are joined by Charles Hanson and Roo Irvine as they dig for antique treasures in Lancashire.

episodes.name: Michelle Hardwick v Amy Robbins
episodes.overview: Actors and friends Michelle Hardwick and Amy Robbins face off in a perky, pillar-box red 1978 MG. They're joined by Margie Cooper and Izzie Balmer for an adventure around Norfolk.

episodes.name: Julie Graham v Tamzin Outhwaite
episodes.overview: Actors Julie Graham and Tamzin Outhwaite are in Sussex in a 1980s Citroen Dyane, assisted by experts Natasha Raskin Sharp and David Harper.

episodes.name: Christine McGuinness v Colson Smith
episodes.overview: Reality TV star Christine McGuinness faces off against her good friend, Coronation Street actor Colson Smith, with experts Irita Marriot and Hettie Jago along for the ride.

episodes.name: Laila Morse v Rita Simons
episodes.overview: EastEnders actors Laila Morse and Rita Simons trawl Devon for antique treasures, with Catherine Southon and Angus Ashworth in tow.

12.name: Series 12
12.overview: Celebrities set off on a road trip around the UK searching for treasures.

episodes.name: Darren Harriott v Anthea Turner
episodes.overview: Anthea Turner and Darren Harriott are with auctioneer Phil Serrell and dealer Ishy Khan in Cambridgeshire. The mighty 1966 Mustang is their chariot of choice.

episodes.name: Harry Clark v Paul Gorton
episodes.overview: After being brutally double-crossed by fellow Traitor Harry Clark, Paul Gorton is back in the Highlands for a second swipe at his rival - this time in the world of antiques.

episodes.name: Roxy Shahidi v Matthew Wolfenden
episodes.overview: Emmerdale love birds and best friends Matthew Wolfenden and Roxy Shahidi shop their way around Yorkshire in a Riley sports saloon, with guidance from Hettie Jago and Steven Moore.
